                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14166144" author="junrao" created="Fri, 10 Oct 2014 01:35:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We probably can wait under &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-1583&quot; title=&quot;Kafka API Refactoring&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-1583&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-1583&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is done since code change will likely be easier then.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14267048" author="gwenshap" created="Wed, 7 Jan 2015 00:20:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created reviewboard &lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.apache.org/r/29647/diff/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://reviews.apache.org/r/29647/diff/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 against branch trunk&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14267057" author="gwenshap" created="Wed, 7 Jan 2015 00:23:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Either I&apos;m missing something or this was trivial &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;From what I can see:&lt;br/&gt;
If acks = 0 || acks = 1, we only append to local log.&lt;br/&gt;
If acks = -1, we produce with delay.&lt;br/&gt;
So I simply removed the part where we count acks in delayed produce. &lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14267940" author="ewencp" created="Wed, 7 Jan 2015 17:51:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;On a related note (which maybe should have been caught in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-1555&quot; title=&quot;provide strong consistency with reasonable availability&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-1555&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-1555&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), the docs on the broker configs is now kind of misleading. Both old and new versions say something like &quot;common values are&quot;, but really the values listed are the only valid options.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14277899" author="gwenshap" created="Wed, 14 Jan 2015 23:41:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated reviewboard &lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.apache.org/r/29647/diff/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://reviews.apache.org/r/29647/diff/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 against branch trunk&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14277902" author="gwenshap" created="Wed, 14 Jan 2015 23:43:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Per &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ewencp&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ewencp&quot;&gt;ewencp&lt;/a&gt;&apos;s suggestion, I added early validation of ack values. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I also wanted to test that validation, which ended up being a rather more involved test than I wanted.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If anyone has suggestions on a simpler way to test API handlers (i.e. without a SocketServer), I&apos;m all ears.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14279037" author="joestein" created="Thu, 15 Jan 2015 18:11:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;With this patch I think we should change the existing functionality with &amp;gt; 1 update to start to LOG as a WARN in the Broker (so it gets people attention to stop using ack &amp;gt;1) but keep everything else the same... the new version of the request (with a match/case) should do the new functionality and we support both.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14286676" author="junrao" created="Thu, 22 Jan 2015 00:49:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;From the discussion in the mailing list, we decided not to bump up the version for the ProduceRequest. Instead, we will log a warning in 0.8.2 that ack&amp;gt;1 will no longer to supported. In 0.8.3, we will throw an exception to requests with ack&amp;gt;1 and remove the support from the code. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=gwenshap&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;gwenshap&quot;&gt;gwenshap&lt;/a&gt;, do you want to update KIP-1 in the wiki accordingly?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14286696" author="gwenshap" created="Thu, 22 Jan 2015 00:59:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated! &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14315329" author="gwenshap" created="Wed, 11 Feb 2015 01:06:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated reviewboard &lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.apache.org/r/29647/diff/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://reviews.apache.org/r/29647/diff/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
